        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">比如</a>：
      </p>
      <p>
        Sentences with nominal predicates use a noun or a nominal endocentric phrase to express a sum of money, a festival,
        a profession, a solar term, a date, or a person's age.
        Sentences with nominal predicates are usually short and simple.
        For example,
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9448' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'míngtiān', 'tomorrow')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">明天</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2635' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Chūyī', 'first day of lunar month / Chinese New Year')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">初一</a>。
