        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">比如</a>：
      </p>
      <p>
        In an elliptical sentence only a part of the whole sentence is spoken because the meaning can be understood from the context.
        Elliptical sentences are often used in conversation. 
        For example,
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          （<a href='/word_detail.php?id=4081' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'nǐ', 'you')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">你</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=825' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '買 mǎi', 'to buy')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">买</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=502' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bù', 'not / no')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">不</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=825' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '買 mǎi', 'to buy')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">买</a>？）（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=321' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'wǒ', 'I / me')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">我</a>）<a href='/word_detail.php?id=502' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bù', 'not / no')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">不</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=825' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '買 mǎi', 'to buy')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">买</a>。 (Are you going to buy it or not?) No. (I am not going to buy it.)<p/>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=20590' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shěng​qù', 'to omit')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">省去</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9249' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '主語 zhǔyǔ', 'subject')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">主语</a>
          (The subject is ommitted.)
        </li>
        <li>
          （<a href='/word_detail.php?id=4081' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'nǐ', 'you')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">你</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=707' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xiǎng', 'to think / to want')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">想</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=4792' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'chī', 'to eat')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">吃</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2707' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '什麼 shénme', 'what')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">什么</a>？）（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=321' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'wǒ', 'I / me')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">我</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=707' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xiǎng', 'to think / to want')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">想</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=4792' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'chī', 'to eat')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">吃</a>）<a href='/word_detail.php?id=4949' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '餃子 jiǎozi', 'Chinese dumplings')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">饺子</a>。 (What would you like to eat?) (I would like to eat) Dumplings.<p/>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=20590' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shěng​qù', 'to omit')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">省去</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9249' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '主語 zhǔyǔ', 'subject')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">主语</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=387' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'hé', 'and')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">和</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9250' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '謂語 wèiyǔ', 'predicate')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">谓语</a>。
          (The subject and predicate are omitted.)
        </li>
        <li>
          （<a href='/word_detail.php?id=3794' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '誰 shéi', 'who')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">谁</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=343' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qù', 'to go')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">去</a>？）<a href='/word_detail.php?id=321' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'wǒ', 'I / me')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">我</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=343' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qù', 'to go')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">去</a>）。 (Who is going?) Me. (I am going)<p/>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=20590' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shěng​qù', 'to omit')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">省去</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9250' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '謂語 wèiyǔ', 'predicate')" 
